<title>UK: UK drug sector shares rise following U.S. gains.</title>
<headline>UK drug sector shares rise following U.S. gains.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-09</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in the British pharmaceutical sector gained on Monday following a strong performance of U.S. drug stocks on Wall Street on Friday, dealers said.</p>
<p>Glaxo Wellcome Plc rose 14 pence to 12.31 stg in London, while Zeneca Group Plc added 16 pence to 18.93-1/2 stg and SmithKline Beecham Plc firmed eight pence to 10.80 stg.</p>
<p>Their gains came after a U.S. drug sector rally helped send propel the Dow sharply higher on Friday.</p>
